HABS-HD Summaries

ATRI Biostatistics

Source: vignettes/HABS-HD-Summaries.Rmd
HABS-HD-Summaries.Rmd

The The Health & Aging Brain Study: Health Disparities (HABS-HD) study (O’Bryant et al. 2021) is a single site project that is conducted at the University of North Texas Health Science Center. The HABS-HD project is funded by grants from the National Institute on Aging (NIA): R01AG054073, R01AG058533. The HABS-HD study has now enrolled over 1,000 Mexican Americans and 1,000 non-Hispanic whites from the community. Enrollment for an additional 1,000 African Americans began February 2021.

The code below demonstrates how to use data in the HABSHD package and R Core Team (2024) to derive some basic summaries.

Baseline characteristics tables 

tableby(CDX_Cog ~ . , data = HD_subjinfo %>% 
    select(-Med_ID, -Visit_ID, -APOE4_rs429358, -APOE4_rs7412)) %>%
  summary(labelTranslations = HD_labels, digits = 1)
